						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar from site No. 13 (Neg. No. 273/55), preserved at the local museum.</p>						

						<p>Ikshvāku Rudrapurushadatta, regnal year 11.</p>						

						<p>Written in Prakrit language and Brāhmī script of 3rd century A.D. (bears the date: year 11 <hi rend="italic">varshā, paksha</hi> 1, <hi rend="italic">divasa</hi> 8).</p>						

						<p>Memorial pillar for Vaṁmabhaṭa, mother of Rudrapurushadatta.</p>						

						<p>(Published in <hi rend="italic">Ep. Ind.,</hi> Vol. XXXIV, pp. 20 ff).</p>						

